1. Write a program in C# Sharp to read 10 numbers from keyboard and find their sum and average .

2.Write a program that reads five numbers from the console and prints the 
greatest of them.

3. Write a program in C# Sharp to read any Month Number in integer and display Month 
name in the word.

4.Write a C# program that prompts the user to enter two integers, if the 
values of the two numbers are equal then return the triple of their sum 
otherwise return their sum.

5. Write an if-statement that takes two integer variables and exchanges
their values if the first one is greater than the second one.

6. Write a C# Sharp program that reads the three sides of a triangle from the console
and check whether a triangle is Equilateral, Isosceles or Scalene.
Hint: Equilateral => 3 equal sides, Isosceles => 2 equal sides, Scalene => No equal sides

